00:00:21,670 --> 00:00:28,700
The first steps towards a sustainable development
was the awareness of our relation with nature.

4
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:35,090
Henry Thoreau was one of the first to sketch
a romantic view on this relation between man

5
00:00:35,090 --> 00:00:44,520
and nature in his book “Walden – or life
in the woods” This was 1854.

6
00:00:44,520 --> 00:00:50,520
A century followed were nature preservation
became more and more important.

7
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:56,860
Followed from the 60th of the last century
by the environmental movement against pollution,

8
00:00:56,860 --> 00:01:03,660
the decreasing of biodiversity and the use
of ending recourses.

9
00:01:03,660 --> 00:01:08,340
The club of Rome put out the following warning
in 1972:

10
00:01:08,340 --> 00:01:14,000
“We broke into Nature's safe deposit box
of fossil carbon,

11
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:20,869
turning it into a wider range of fuels,
and potentially destabilizing the global climate

12
00:01:20,869 --> 00:01:26,270
in the process.” The awareness of some was
vital,

13
00:01:26,270 --> 00:01:30,539
jet it didn’t change the world for the better.

14
00:01:30,539 --> 00:01:33,310
To do this,
a new perspective was needed:

15
00:01:33,310 --> 00:01:34,420
‘Social sustainability or ‘People’.

16
00:01:34,420 --> 00:01:41,020
We had to wait until 1992 at the Rio Earth
Summit.

17
00:01:41,020 --> 00:01:45,170
The central conclusion of this summit was
that:

18
00:01:45,170 --> 00:01:50,240
Human beings are at the centre of concerns
for sustainable development.

19
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:58,329
They are entitled to a healthy and productive
life in harmony with nature.

20
00:01:58,329 --> 00:02:04,529
So the ecological awareness first shifted
towards an environmental awareness and now

21
00:02:04,529 --> 00:02:06,590
people were included.

22
00:02:06,590 --> 00:02:12,160
The involvement of the laymen,
the wellbeing of the end-users became central

23
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:13,720
themes.

24
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:19,190
People were part of the problem,
but they are also the reason to find solutions

25
00:02:19,190 --> 00:02:22,140
and they ARE the solutions.

26
