If we start with the wellbeing of people,
we take the perspective of the World Health

28
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:19,890
Organisation.

29
00:03:19,890 --> 00:03:27,030
In a liveable city we fulfilling basic needs
of all and emphasizing the needs of the vulnerable

30
00:03:27,030 --> 00:03:28,940
groups.

31
00:03:28,940 --> 00:03:34,380
Basic needs are health and safety,
being free from war and hunger.

32
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:38,030
Linked topic is happiness.

33
00:03:38,030 --> 00:03:42,310
Emphasizing the needs of vulnerable groups
is paying attention to children,

34
00:03:42,310 --> 00:03:44,940
elderly,
the urban poor,

35
00:03:44,940 --> 00:03:46,780
disabled,
etc.

36
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:51,670
A child friendly city is friendly for all.

37
00:03:51,670 --> 00:04:00,860
A city were wayfinding is based on the capacity
of old people is more accessible for all.

38
00:04:00,860 --> 00:04:04,930
Environmental awareness of citizen is one
step,

39
00:04:04,930 --> 00:04:09,960
participation and co-shaping the sustainable
city is another step.

40
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:16,280
Of course also the sustainability awareness
and participation of other actors are vital

41
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:18,180
here,
like governance,

42
00:04:18,180 --> 00:04:25,509
designers and all actors involved in shaping
and maintaining the city.

43
00:04:25,509 --> 00:04:32,180
The definition of Brundtland speaks of the
needs of future generations.

44
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:36,030
This includes two questions:
First:

45
00:04:36,030 --> 00:04:40,820
To what extent are people willing to adjust
their behaviour to what is best for people

46
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:43,720
over 20 to 50 years?

47
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:50,350
Most people cannot oversee the impact of their
behaviour of today on their wellbeing tomorrow.

48
00:04:50,350 --> 00:04:54,170
During the first traffic-jam in the Netherlands
in 1955,

49
00:04:54,170 --> 00:04:58,860
people were filled with joy;
overseeing so much luxury.

50
00:04:58,860 --> 00:05:02,139
More cars are only better!

51
00:05:02,139 --> 00:05:07,000
Secondly;
What are the needs of a next generation?

52
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:13,430
This is why we emphasis basic needs;
